The Genius You’ve Never Heard Of: Luke Farritor, the Prodigy Behind Elon Musk's Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE)

Luke Farritor, a 23-year-old software engineer from Lincoln, Nebraska, has recently garnered attention for his pivotal role in Elon Musk's Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE). Established under President Donald Trump's administration, DOGE aims to streamline federal operations and reduce government spending. Farritor's involvement in this initiative has sparked both interest and controversy, especially given his background in artificial intelligence and his spectacular discoveries—most notably his work deciphering ancient scrolls using machine learning, which earned him international recognition.
